                "title_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Applied Math. and Computational Math. Individual (5 problems) "
                    }
                ],
                "level": 1
            },
            "bbox": [
                189,
                131,
                786,
                178
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 1. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "s"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be relatively prime positive integers. Prove that the number of lattice paths from "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( 0 , 0 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "to "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( r , s )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", which consists of steps "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( 1 , 0 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "( 0 , 1 )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and never go above the line "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "r y = s x"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is given by "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                225,
                860,
                275
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {1}{r + s} \\left( \\begin{array}{c} r + s \\\\ s \\end{array} \\right).",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/83e0cefbcead513e573c14d49a62e50dc5640850d2a23fedd8830c2169f1907a.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                426,
                284,
                549,
                319
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 2. The following "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "2 \\times 2"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "block matrix "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                115,
                338,
                524,
                354
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "C (\\alpha) = \\left[ \\begin{array}{c c} \\alpha I & A \\\\ A ^ {T} & 0 \\end{array} \\right]",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/96a1dee5fe79d6b8b5c6df93a9074398c6c68e4e668cc3493e1331197812f0c5.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                403,
                362,
                571,
                399
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "plays a key role in an augmented system method to solve linear least squares problem, a fundamental numerical linear algebra problem for fitting a linear model to observations subject to errors in science, where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { m \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is of full rank "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "n \\leq m"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "I"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "m \\times m"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "identity matrix, and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha \\geq 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Prove the following results which address the question of optimal choice of scaling "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for stabiltiy of the augmented system method. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                406,
                860,
                489
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(a) The eigenvalues of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C ( \\alpha )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                144,
                493,
                428,
                511
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {\\alpha}{2} \\pm \\left(\\frac {\\alpha^ {2}}{4} + \\sigma_ {i} ^ {2}\\right) ^ {1 / 2} \\quad \\mathrm {f o r} i = 1, 2, \\ldots , n, \\quad \\mathrm {a n d} \\quad \\alpha \\quad (m - n \\mathrm {t i m e s}),",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/1c97f7c891d986aae74870e528f4587e2c573f483464ebbfc924e564940ef07c.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                201,
                519,
                776,
                560
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sigma _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "i = 1 , 2 , \\ldots , n"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are the singular values of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", arranged in the decreasing order, i.e., "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sigma _ { 1 } \\geq \\sigma _ { 2 } \\geq \\cdot \\cdot \\cdot \\geq \\sigma _ { n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                176,
                565,
                858,
                598
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "(b) The condition number "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\kappa _ { 2 } ( C ( \\alpha ) ) = \\| C ( \\alpha ) \\| _ { 2 } \\| [ C ( \\alpha ) ] ^ { - 1 } \\| _ { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "has the following bounds: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                144,
                599,
                873,
                617
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sqrt {2} \\kappa_ {2} (A) \\leq \\min _ {\\alpha} \\kappa_ {2} (C (\\alpha)) \\leq 2 \\kappa_ {2} (A),",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/9f6bbc22472a27fc3845dd7b039669d74316ecc1fafa3a7004054441064970a0.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                334,
                625,
                645,
                650
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "with "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathrm { m i n } _ { \\alpha } \\kappa _ { 2 } ( C ( \\alpha ) )"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "being achieved for "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\alpha = \\sigma _ { n } / \\sqrt { 2 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                176,
                659,
                663,
                678
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\max _ {\\alpha} \\kappa_ {2} (C (\\alpha)) > \\kappa_ {2} (A) ^ {2},",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/3e3257968f385df568c705bfcfd7e92f168aecbee672e4e38cdffe785202e80d.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                383,
                686,
                594,
                709
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\| \\cdot \\|"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is the spectral norm of a matrix. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                176,
                718,
                563,
                734
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Recall that any matrix "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { m \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "has a singular value decomposition (SVD): "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                115,
                739,
                788,
                757
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "A = U \\Sigma V ^ {T}, \\quad \\Sigma = \\mathrm {d i a g} (\\sigma_ {1}, \\sigma_ {2}, \\ldots , \\sigma_ {p}) \\in \\mathbf {R} ^ {m \\times n}, \\quad p = \\min (m, n),",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/61962832350d0fd422fa6a5d5eccc4239d8efc4e1d72fbfc85cdfd985b132f46.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                205,
                765,
                771,
                785
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sigma _ { 1 } \\geq \\sigma _ { 2 } \\geq \\cdot \\cdot \\cdot \\geq \\sigma _ { p } \\geq 0"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { m \\times m }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V \\in \\mathbf { R } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are both orthogonal. The "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\sigma _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are the singular values of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and the columns of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are the left and right singular vectors of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", respectively. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                791,
                860,
                843
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "page_number",
            "content": {
                "page_number_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1 "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                482,
                857,
                494,
                866
            ]
        }
    ],
    [
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 3. Solve the following linear hyperbolic partial differential equation "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                115,
                109,
                794,
                127
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "u _ {t} + a u _ {x} = 0, \\quad t \\geq 0, \\tag {1}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/8d069579de0615041013b535fd67f3c87379ae9c2165efe7e5a9c9f74030215e.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                117,
                131,
                584,
                149
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "a"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a constant. Using the finite difference approximation, we can obtain the forward-time central-space scheme as follows, "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                154,
                860,
                187
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\frac {u _ {m} ^ {n + 1} - u _ {m} ^ {n}}{k} + a \\frac {u _ {m + 1} ^ {n} - u _ {m - 1} ^ {n}}{2 h} = 0, \\tag {2}",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/be65d76f49d034383f916ab5a0c6dbd3bfc1643253c089f1a31e5e82b7ab4f45.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                117,
                191,
                631,
                225
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "k"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "h"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are temporal and spatial mesh sizes. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                115,
                228,
                564,
                244
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(a) Show that when we fix "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\lambda = k / h"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "as a positive constant, the forward-time centralspace scheme (2) is consistent with equation (1). "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(b) Analyze the stability of this method. Is the method stable with "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\lambda = k / h"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "being fixed as a constant? "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(c) How would the answer change if you are allowed to make "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\lambda = k / h"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "small? "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(d) Would this is a good scheme to use even if you can make it stable by making "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\lambda"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "small? If not, please provide a simple modification to make this scheme stable by keeping "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\lambda"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "fixed. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                142,
                247,
                857,
                376
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 4. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A , H , Q \\in \\mathbb { C } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is non-singular. Assume that "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H = Q ^ { - 1 } A Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "H"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is properly upper Hessenberg. Show that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                390,
                860,
                424
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\operatorname {s p a n} \\left\\{q _ {1}, q _ {2}, \\dots , q _ {j} \\right\\} = \\mathcal {K} _ {j} (A, q _ {1}), \\quad j = 1, 2, \\dots , n",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/c0d117cc70c269605dd083f70a3cdf1d58dc03938911e3c5f1d57605afb03469.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                265,
                429,
                709,
                448
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "q _ { j }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is the "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "j"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "-th column of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "Q"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "{ \\cal K } _ { j } ( A , q _ { 1 } ) = \\mathrm { s p a n } \\{ q _ { 1 } , A q _ { 1 } , \\ldots , A ^ { j - 1 } q _ { 1 } \\} ."
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                451,
                779,
                470
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Problem 5. Minkowski Problem. "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                115,
                479,
                442,
                495
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "image",
            "content": {
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/c9aa66d7f3fa71aee892c128f678b8fd0134eeba35d6dff1e42e18157c2c628c.jpg"
                },
                "image_caption": [],
                "image_footnote": []
            },
            "bbox": [
                357,
                499,
                623,
                684
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Assume "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "P"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is a convex polyhedron embedded in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { R } ^ { 3 }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the faces are "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\{ F _ { 1 } , F _ { 2 } , \\cdots , F _ { k } \\}"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the unit normal vector to the face "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "F _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbf { n } _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", the area of "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "F _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "is "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A _ { i }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "1 \\leq i \\leq k"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                114,
                700,
                858,
                734
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "• Show that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                159,
                736,
                272,
                751
            ]
